content:
Add a Number Input element on a FlexCard to enable users to select from a range of numbers you specify.

From the Properties panel, configure properties and custom attributes, add an action, and add conditions.

REQUIRED VERSIONS

Available beginning Winter '22.

Configure properties common to all Input elements:

Field Binding: bind the value of the input element to an existing or new data field.
Field Label: enter the label that appears next to the element.
Read-only: disable the ability to modify the input values.
Help Text: enter helpful text about the purpose of the input field.

Configure additional properties:

Attribute: select from an attribute in the dropdown.
Value: enter a value for the attribute.

To execute an action when a user interacts with the input element, click + Add Action.
To add conditions that must be met for the element to display, see Add Conditions to a FlexCard Element.
To style your element, click Style to open the Style panel.
title: Adding Range Input Element to FlexCards
